article.headline: San Diego 29, Davidson 15
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Godfrey Smith caught nine passes for 184 yards and three touchdowns, and San Diego defeated Davidson 29-15 on Saturday. Smith was the favorite target of quarterback Mason Mills, who completed 17 of 27 passes for 240 yards and three touchdowns. San Diego (5-6, 5-3 Pioneer League), scored 15 points in the final quarter to rally for the win. Phil Morelli scored on a 4-yard run with 13 minutes to play, then Mills connected with Smith on a 27-yard touchdown pass play with 4:10 remaining to put the game away. The Toreros' defense held Davidson to minus-10 yards rushing and sacked quarterback Jonathan Carkhuff eight times. Davidson (3-7, 3-5) built a 15-14 lead after three quarters on the strength of two touchdown passes by Carkhuff, who was 16-of-27 for 258 yards.
